Nkazimulo Khumalo has just graduated with a Bachelor's Degree in Education from Unisa. JOHANNESBURG - One taxi driver has proved that anything is possible if you're prepared to work hard. Nkazimulo Khumalo has just graduated with a Bachelor's Degree in Education from Unisa. The 28-year-old found time to study in between driving passengers in a taxi. He now wants to teach in township schools to help motivate children to chase their dreams. Khumalo said he's long wanted to be a teacher and started studying in 2015. "I always told myself that I wanted to be a teacher," he said. "I'm happy. Good things are coming." Khumalo said he kept his studies a secret from his passengers. "Most of my colleagues were surprised when I graduated," he said.